{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_evans_ver01/data/sn86063730/00332894195/1930022201/0399.xml":{"full_text":"if Hnmmsuflle Herald\nEstablished July 4, 1892\nEntered as second-class matter in the Poetoftlcs\nBrownsville. Texas.\nTHE BROWNSVILLE HERALD PUBLISHING\nCOMPANY\nSubscription Rates\u2014Dally and Sunday (7 Issues)\nDne Year\n31x Months .$4.50\nThree Months.$2.25\nDne Month. .75\nMEMBER OP THE ASSOCIATED PRESS\nThe Associated Press is exclusively entitled to the use\nfor publication of all news dispatches credited to It or\nnot otherwise credited in this paper, and also the\nlocal news published herein.\nHarlingen Office. Reese-Wll-Mond Hotel. Phone 1020.\nTEXAS DAILY PRESS LEAGUB\nNational Advertising Representatives\nDallas. Texas, 512 Mercantile Bank Building.\nKansas City. Mo, 306 Coca Cola Building.\nChicago, 111, Association Building.\nNew York. 350 Madison Avenue.\nSt. Louis. 502 Star Building.\nLos Angeles. Cal, Room 1015 New Orpheum Bldg,\n846 S. Broadway.\n8an Francisco. Cal, 318 Kohl Building.\n\u2018I Want to Join Your Mother*\nf \u201cDon't give me any medicine to keep me here. 1\nwant to Join your mother,\" said Capt. Pat Dolan to\nhis children who had gathered around his bedside.\nTheir mother had died 19 days before. Then he\nturned his face to the wall and it was all over.\nCapt. Pat Dolan was 86 He was born in Ireland.\nHe fought on the federal side during the war. After\nthe surrender of Lee he located in Texas. He pur\nchased a ranch near Uvalde. He became a noted\nTexas ranger. He fought outlaws. Mexicans and men\nof his own tongue on the Rio Grande river from\nBrownsville to El Paso.\nEl Paso became his home. There the wife of 56\nyears passed on to her reward. 'T want to go, too. I\ncan\u2019t stay here without iter,\" lie said. After the fu\nneral of his beloved partner he took to his bed. He\nnever got up again.\nHe was a picturesque figure and widely known on\naoth sides of the Rio Grande. He was a warrior in\nwartime and as mild as a Quaker in peace time. He\nloved one woman. She was his pal for 56 years, and\nwhen she passed on his sole ambition was to join her\nla the shade of the trees on the eternity side of the\nInvisible river.\nA real human interest story, not a sob story, but\nthe tale of a fighting man who was more than will\ning to embark on the greatest and last of great ad\nventures that fall to the lot of the mortals on this\nmundane sphere, enjoy a brief existence and then\npass out of the picture as noiselessly as they entered\nIt at the beginning of life\u2019s brief span here below.\nSons of Wild Jackasses Organize\nWhite Bear is a Minnesota farm center. White j\nScar has organized the first \u201cSONS OF WILD JACK- j\nASSES CLUB,\u201d with a list of 200 charter members.\nIts purpose is to \u201cbray for fair treatment for the\nfarmer.\u201d A white badge, the size of a half dollar, and\npicturing a jackass with his hind feet In the air, is\nthe emblem of the club.\nName and button have been copyrighted and its\npromoters say that It Is going to sweep the farm\nlands of the west and the northwest like fire sweeps\nthe dead prairie grass in fall time. Sen. George H\nMoses of New Hampshire started something when\nhe branded champions of farm legislation as \u201csons\nof wild jackasses.\u201d\nReady to Educate Texas Indians\nTexas Indians are to be given a place In the edu\ncational picture. Worthy and capable members of\nthe Alabama and Coushatta Indian tribes in Polk\ncounty will be admitted to the government Indian\nschools Including Haskell Institute at Lawrence.\nKan. All pupils must meet requirements as to de\ngree of blood and absence of available local school\nfacilities\nOf course it Is understood that children of the\nTammy tribe of Indians in the cities of Dallas.\nFort Worth. Houston. San Antonio and elsewhere are\nbarred They hare local school facilities ar.d are in\nno sense wards of the Great White Fathers on the\nbanks of the Potomac.\nI\nPOLITENESS ON THE HIGH SEAS\n(Copyright, 1930, by The Associated Newspapers.)\nHie major powers cannot agree to abolish the sub\nmarine, it is announced, but will \u201chumanise\" their\noperations. In other words the U-boats will be more\npolite. There may even be a Book of Submarine Eti\nquette by some naval Emily Post. Questions bound\nto arise are:\n1. \u2014Should a submarine speak to a vessel to which\nit has not been Introduced?\n2. \u2014What should the well dressed submarine skip\nper wear (a) when sinking a ship in the morning (b)\nin the afternoon (c) at night?\n3. \u2014Is it proper, in fact, for a submarine to pay in\nformal calls before noon?\n4. \u2014On what occasions is it considered imperative\nfor a submarine to rise?\n5. \u2014Is it ever excusable for a merchant to keep a\nU-boat waiting?\n6. \u2014Is it ever good manners for a submarine to can\ncel a sinking after sending out announcements?\n7. \u2014What are the correct forms of apology to steam\nship tourists whose vessel has been sunk under them?\n8. \u2014How long should a submarine captain know a\nmerchant ship before torpedoing it?\n9. \u2014How should a gentleman help a single lady out\nof the ocean? A married lady? A widow?\n10. \u2014What is the proper greeting to a strange ship\nby a well-bred submarine. Is \u201cHaven't I seen you\nsome place before?\u201d or \"Pardon me. but didn't I meet\nyou once in the English Channel?\" ever permissible?\nif*\nSubmarines, several naval powers insist, are all\nright if they know the rules of good behavior and\nare not rough and uncouth. The trouble with those\nused in the last war was that they had no manners.\n\nThis led to considerable hard feelings, which all\nthe naval powers are anxious to avoid. It is possible,\nthey held, to blow up a ship without leaving an un\nfavorable impression. Everything depends on the\nright touch.\n\nNo submarine captain wants to be so rude that he\nwill never be asked to sink anybody a second time.\n\nThere may even be cards issued by submarine skip\npers before the event:\nCAPTAIN MAX SULZERBERGER\nRequests\nThe Pleasure of Your Company\nAt a Torpedoing\nWednesday, June 8th, at 3 p. m\n\nBy all means humanize the submarine. Anything\nto make warfare all in good fun.\nCAN'T IT BE STOPPED BT THE MONROE\nDOCTRINE?\nMiss America, Miss Europe, Miss Asia. Miss Great\nBritain and the other misses are to meet at Rio Dc\nJaneiro for the title of Miss Universe. This disposes\nof the belief that South America doesn't want any\nwars.\nIn a cigarette price war between two metropolitan\ndepartment stores cartons sold as low as 74 cents.\nIt is not very often one gets a chance to acquire a\ncough cure, complete nonchalance and a u eight ic\nducer at that price.\nReady for the Sport of Kings\nWith only one dissenting vote the Texas associa\ntion of fair secretaries placed itself squarely behind\nthe Avis racing bill. A year ago. despite heated ar\nguments over the horse racing proposition, the as\nsociation took no action other than to declare its\nbelief that the matter was one for local fair decision.\nAll this is a reminder that Arlington Downs is one\nof the finest horse breeding enterprises in America\nwith a plant that is second to none under American\nskies.\n\u2018So This Is Texas*\nBandits run not in Dallas.'' is the startling head\nline above a news story in a Dallas paper. Dallas is\nthe home of Lieut, Gov. Barry Miller. Dallas is the\nhome of Dr. Atticus Webb. Dallas ts the home of\nthousands of reformers and uplifters and welfare\nworkers. Now why should bandits run riot in Dal\nlas?\"\nTHE OLD HOME TOWN Stanley\n'THAT 5 JUST UFC FOR YOU,\nI HEARD OF A FELLER WHO\nWAS A DARE DEVIL. PARACHUTE\nJUMPER, AND OH H\u00bbS VACAT/ON-\nHE fell out of A Rockin' J\nI CHAIR AND BROKE HIS\nNECK\nDAO <SUMMlT-lVE\nBEEN HANDUN SHARP\nKNIVES FOR YEA\nAND THATS THE\nFIRST TIME I EVER]\nDREW Blood-- J\nPan<* nr!'\nV R) Htfi c\nC \u00bbN THE Clarion,\n(THERE S A STORY J\nBout a uion\nTamer who C\nDied prom a\nMOSQUITO\nX Bite r.j #JrJ\n->\u2022\u00bb-r\nRERShVogaN^THE LOCAL WOOD carver and\nprofessional fancy whittl.er^ darn near\ncut off his finger today.while\nSHARPENING a NICKEL. LEAD PENCIL\ne >i\u00bb ui w a_'_\u00a3ll2\u00a3_\nChrist\u2019s School for Service\n\n\u201cBrass Tacks\u201d on the Sunday School Lesson\n(The (froldett (Text\n\u201cThe harvest truly is plenteous, but the labourers are few; Pray\ny therefore the Lord of the harvest, that he will send forth laboureri\ninto bis harvest.\"\u2014Matthew 9:37, 38.\nTHE GOLDEN TEXT\nBy Dr. ALVIN E. BELL\nThe king who has enunciated the\nfundamental principles of his king\ndom in the Sermon on the Mount\nand presented the credentials of\nhis royalty in many marvelous\nmiracles, soon finds the fruits ol\nhis ministry increasing to the point\nwhere he must call assistants to\nshare the work with him. Accord\ningly, the king selects from his\ndisciples a cabinet of twelve mem\nbers. men who have been with him\nfrom the beginning, who are now to\nshare his work of telling the people\nabout his kingdom.\ntrowds f iBw t ompassion\nA crowd is always an interesting\nstudy. To the politician crowds\nmean potential votes; to a salesman\nthey are potential buyers; but tG\nthe Lord Jesus they were crowds\nof souls in need of sustenance and\nsalvation. \u201cBut when he saw the\nmultitudes, he was moved with\ncompassion on them, because they\nfainted, and were scattered abroad,\nas sheep having no shepherd. Then\nsaith he until his disciples, the\nharvest truly is plenteous, but the\nlaborers are few. pray ye therefore\nthe Lord of the harvest, that he\nwill send forth laborers into his\nharvest.\u201d Thus the first require\nment of thsoe who would help meet\nthe needs of their fe\u2019.lowmen crowd\ning the highways of life is compas\nsion. sympathy, ability to under\nstand and enter unto fellowship\nwith them in their deepest needs\nand longings. Hard-boiled profes\nsionalism. however skilled in other\nrespects, will fail utterly in minis\ntering to the troubled crowds be\ncause their deepest and most basic\nneeds are appreciated only by\nthose who. like their Master. \"See\ning the multitudes are moved with\ncompassion on them.\u201d\nLuke tells us how at this time\nJesus \u201cwent out Into a mountain to\npray, and continued all night in\nprayer to Ciod. And when it was\nday. he called unto him his disciples:\nand of them he chose twelve, whom\nalso he named aixjstles.\" Mary adds\nthe significant note, That they\nshould be with him. and that he\nmight send them forth.\u201d An \u2022\u2022Apos\ntle' means \"a sent one.\u201d Eut before\nthey could be \u201csent forth\u201d they\nmust \u201cbe with him.\u201d That was\ntheir apprenticeship, and it must\nbe ours. The apost'.e must first be\na disciple, a learner. There is no\nshort cut to service of the multi\ntudes that omits this essential pre\nparation. \u201cThe harvest truly was\nplenteous, and the laborers few,\u201d\nbut despite this urgency the labor\ners must be prepared, though it\ncost three precious years of the\nprime of their lives and of their\nMaster's. Modern youth, eager to\nanswer the challenge of ripened\nharvests must pay the price of pre\nparation. Never was it demanded\nmore insistently than in this pres\nent age.\nEmpowered for Service\nThis month of memories of Lin\ncoln and Washington testifies that\nwhen Chris: sends us forth to a\ngreat task he empowers us. identi\nfies himself with us and sticks bv\nus to see us through. \u201cWhen he had\npalled unto him his twelve disciples,\nhe gave them power, etc.\" \u201cHe that\nreceive?!! you receiveth me.\u201d And\nto us he promises the same pres\nence and power undiminshed: \u201cLo.\nI am with you always, even unto\nthe end of the world.\"\n<The Internationa! Uniform Les\nson for Feb. 23 is Matt. 9:35-10*.\n40-42. the subject being \u201cThe\nTwelve Sent Forth and the Gold\nen Text. Matt. 0 37. 38. \u201cThe Harv\n.-'st indeed is plenteous, but the\nj laborer arc few. Prav we therefore\nthe l/!rd of the harvest, that he\n1 send forth laborers into his harv\nest.\u201d)\n<The Daily Bible Readings for\nnext week's study are: Mon.. Matt.\n11:1-6: Tues, Matt. 11:25-30; Wed.\nMatt. 12:1-8; Thurs Matt. 10:13-20;\nFrL John 1:43-51; Sat.. John 14:1\n11. and Sun, Isa 61:1-9.)\nMOVIE SIDELIGHTS\nARC APIA \u2014HARLINGEN\nJanet Gaynor and Charles Far\nrell are co-stars of the movietone\nmusical comedy romance, Sunny\nSide Up\u201d booked for a Saturday\nmidnight Matinee and Sunday. Mon\nday. Tuesday showmgs at the Har\nlingen, Arcadia Theatre.\nThe dainty, wistful little Janet\nproves her versatility by playing a\ncomedy role, broad in spots, and\nagain on the border land of pathos.\nShe sings, she dances she talks and\nshe does it all with that touch of\ngenius that has raised her from the\nrear ranks of extra girls to the\nfront rank of the greatest stars in\nthe entertainment world.\nFarrell, too. Is called upon to en\nact an entirely different sort of role\nthan he ever essayed before, and\nhe does it with a dash and finish\nthat stamps him as a superlative\nactor.\nThere are at least six tremendous\nsong hits in \"Sunny Side Up,\u201d in\ncluding \"A Talking Picture of You.\u201d\n\"Sunny Side Up.\" \"I'm a Dreamer.\"\n'Turn on the Heat.\u201d \"You Find the\nTime, I'll Find tlie Place.\u201d and\nSAMBO\u2019S PHILOSOPHY\nan\u2019 den Ol* Miss done fill\nbofe o' dem hnski:3 plumb, span*\nFULL! Lawsy, me. who tla\nMOULDIN' be THANKFUL! Ua\nheaab-hah, LowdM\u201d\n\u201cYou've Got Me Pickin\u2019 Petals Off\nof Daisies.\"\nPALACE \u2014McALLEN\nKing Vidor seems to be about the\nideal directorial agency for Marion\nDavies.\nIn \"Not So Dumb\u201d Metro-Gold\nwyn-Mayer\u2019s new starring vehicle\nfor the comedienne, which opened\nlast night at the Palace, McAllen,\nVidor has provided her with the\nmost vivacious role she has played, a\nsparkling vehicle that affords rare\ncomedy talents.\nThe picture is an adaption of the\nwell-known stage farce. \"Dulcy,\"\nby George S. Kaufman and Marc\nConnelly. It is Vidor's third pic\nture with Miss Davies as the star,\nthe previous two having been the\nexceptionally successful \"The Patsy\"\nand \"Show People.\"\nMiss Davies demonstrates her\nvocal as well as physical versatility\nin the screen comedy, adapting her\nvoice as well as her personality to\nthe role of a blundering flapper\nwho tries to run her fiance's busi\nness affairs and almost ruins her\nromance as well as his bank ac\ncount.\nLocal Presbyterian\nMen to Attend Meet\nA meeting for rtfen will be held\nat the San Benito Presbyterian\nChurch Saturday. 8:00 p. m. and\nSunday at 3.00 p. m. Dr. J. E. Pur\ncell of Atlanta. Ga.. and Dr. L. E.\nSelfridge of San Antonio will be\nthe speakers. A delegation of men\nwill attend from the local Presby\nterian church.\nEAT DELICIOUS\nORANGES FOR HEALTH\nGet ft bushel for ft dollar. See\nMatt Brown at Pip**r Stiles\nPlantation or Haney C. Stiles,\nTraveler\u2019s Hotel\nIiv the Chirches\nFIRST PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH\nElizabeth St. and Palm. Boulevard.\n9:45 a. m. Sunday School, Cleve\nTandy, Supt. Miss Frances Shive,\ndirector of religious education.\n11:00 a. m. Morning worship.\nPrelude. \"Offertoire in F\u201d\u2014\n(Higgs);\nAnthem. Selected;\nOffertory-Moment Rellgleux\"\n(Frilm);\nChildren\u2019s story\u2014Miss Fern Day,\nSermon\u2014\"Obeying the Heavenly\nVision\".\nPostlude\u2014\"Postlude\" (Liebig)\n6:30 p. m.. Senior League. Topic,\n\"The Bible for all nations.\" Miss\nAnn Garner, leader.\n7:30 D. m. Evening worship\nPreluae\u2014\"Idyl\" (Bullis);\nOffertory\u2014 \"A Vesper Prayer\u201d\n(Diggle);\nAnthem, Selected:\nSermon, \u2022Positive Christianity*\u2019;\nPostlude\u2014\u2022Postlude\u201d (Parker)\nJ. A. Russell, musical director;\nMjs. A. B. Niven, organist.\nMonday, 3:30 p. m.. the womans\nauxiliary will hold their regular\nmonthly social meeting at the\nchurch with Circle No. 1 hostess.\nMonday, 7:30 p. m., important\nmeeting of the officers of the church.\nEvery officer urged to be present.\nTuesday, 4:30 p. m., Junior league.\nTuesday, 7:30 p. m. Senior League\nCouncil meeting.\nThursday night, choir rehearsel\nFriday night. Boy Scout meeting.\nLet us welcome you to the fellow\nship of our service.\nEmmet P. Day, Pastor.\nCHRISTIAN SCIENCE SOCIETY\nCor. Elizabeth and West Second Sts.\nChristian Science Society of\nBrownsville, Texas, a branch of\nThe Mother Church. First Church\nof Christ. Scientist in Boston, Mas\nsachusetts.\nSundav school at 9:45 a. m.\nSunday morning services at 11:00.\nSubject: \u2022Mind\u201d.\nA Wednesday evening testimonial\nmeeting at 8:00 o\u2019clock.\nReading room in the church\nbuilding open Tuesdays and Fri\ndays from 3:00 to 5:00 p. m.\nFIRST BAPTIST CHURCH\n9:45 Gra4ed and Departmentlaed\nSunday School. Ewing D. Clark,\nSup't.\n10:55 Morning Worship:\nPrelude\u2014Allegro Maestoso\u2014West\nDoxology\u2014 Invocation\u2014 Gloria\nPatria.\nHymn 48.\nScripture Reading\nHymn 319\nOffertory\u2014Gounod\nAnthem\u2014\"Lift Up Your Heads O\nYe Gates\u2019\u2014Ashford.\nSermon by the Pastor:\n\u201cThe Faith\u201d or The Marks of\nThe New Testament Church.\"\nHymn 173.\nPostlude\u2014Festival March\u2014 Starck\n6 30 Graded and Dcpartmentized\nB Y. P U. W E. Collins General\nDirector.\n7:30 Evening Worship:\nPrelude\u2014Flagler\nHymn 465\nPrayer\nHymn 37\nOffertory\u2014Romance\u2014Shelly\nTrio\u2014\"I am the Light of the\nWorld\u201d\u2014Coeme.\nSung by Mdsmes. E. J. Tucker. F.\nJ. Schmidt and Miss Gladys Wood\ni rome.\nSermon by tnc pastor: incme.\nDetective Faith.\nHymn 28.\nPostiude\u2014Allegretto\u2014 Volkmann.\nIndividuals who wonder why\nthere are so many churches of\ndifferent faith and order may be\ninterested in hearing the moimlng\nmessage. Surely the New Testament\nchurches had sufficient -ear marks\"\nthat we may discover them. You\nwill receive a cordial welcome what\never vour traditional faith may\nhave been. Let us look within the\nsacred Volume Sunday morning.\nO. L. Smith. Pastor\nLUTHERAN CHURCH\nThe Evangelical Lutheran Mls\nnon of the United Lutheran church\nin America; services at the Epis\ncopal parish house at 3pm A\nheartv welcome. Rev. N. Scheffer,\npastor.\nFIRST METHODIST CHURCH\n9.30 Sunday school. Men\u2019s Bible\nclass meet at Queen theater. W.\nW. Underwood, Supt.\n10:50 Morning Worship service.\nPrelude -Andante\u201d (Tsehaikow\nsky), Hymn, -Apostles Creed.\u201d\nATTENTION! j\nWe have added a\nRental Library to our\nstore! Come in and look\nit over. All of the best j\nsellers of all publishers\nKeep abreast of the\nmost popular new book: i\nby renting them a\u2019 j\nsmall cost!\nHARGROVE\u2019S i\nStationery Book Store\nPhone 348\nBrownsville, Texas\nMEND-A-RUN SHOP\nDon't throw your Silk Hose\naway! Let Mrs. Barbara Os\ntrander mend the runs and\nsnags. All Work Guaranteed.\nMRS. ANNA NORLIXG\u2019S\nCORSET SHOP\n1327 Elizabeth Brownsville\nFEED GRAIN\nAND\nHAY\nMcLELLAND FEED CO.,\nPhone 765 508 N. Commerce\nHarlingen\nEat At\nAnthony\u2019s Waffle\nShop\n517 12 St Phone 983\n\nprayer. Hymn. 8crlpture reading\nfrom Psalm* \"Gloria Patrl,\u201d Of\nfertory, \"Angelus\u201d (Mossonel), 8o.\u2019o\nSupplication, Mrs. Sutherland, Ser\nmon \"Gods Plans Not as Our\nPlans,\u201d Postlude.\n6:30 p. m. Epworth League meet.\n7:30 Evening Worship Service.\nPrelude (Bercuese* (Schytte),\nHymn no. Prayer, Hymn, Offertory\n\u2018Coronation\" tMeyebeer), Quartet\nte The Harmony Foursome, Sermon\nby pastor. Postlude \"Intermezzo\"\n(Mascogrl)\n3:00 p. m. Woman's Missionary\nSociety. Monday.\n7:30 p. m. Wednesday, Mission\nStudy class.\nCENTRAL CHRISTIAN CHURCH\nTwelfth and Jefferson Streets.\n(Masonic Temple)\n9:45 a. m. Bible School. Sher\nwood Bishop, superintendent.\n11:00 a. m. Morning and Com\nmunion service.\n11:20 a. m. Sermon\u2014\"The Unity\nof The Church\"\u2014Dr. S. K. Hallam.\n6:30 p. m. Christian Endeavor\nProgram.\n7 30 p. m. Evening Worship.\n8:00 p. m. Sermon\u2014\"Now and\nNow\u2014Not By and By\"\u2014Geo. F\nDennis.\nSinging Evangelist, E. M. Dout\nhett, will sing at the evening serv\nice.\nAMERICAN SPIRITUALISTIC\nHarlingen\nThe Rev. E. V. Sloots will lecture\non the power of God at the Sun\nday evening service. He will be as\nsisted by Mrs. Aug. Barber. Service\nbegins 7:30 p. m.\nAt the Odd Fellows hall, N. P.\nand West Monroe.\nCHRISTIAN UNITY\n509 Elizabeth St.\n9:45-10:45 a. m. Sunday Services.\n8 p. m.\u2014Wednesday, song and\nprayer service, testimonials.\n9:30 a. m.\u2014 Tuesday, workers'\nmeeting.\n3-4 p. m.\u2014Friday, study classes\nconducted by Mrs. Thomas.\nMrs. Thomas in office each\nmorning, 9 to 11:30.\nLUTHERAN CHURCH\nRev. H. L. Wledranders, Pastor.\nServices ever: Sunday in the\nJunior High school auditorium at\n9 a. m. Sunday School at 10 a. m.\nVOLUNTEERS OF AMERICA\n820 Elizabeth St.\n7:30 p. m.. preaching service.\nPrayer meeting weekly at 7:30\np. m.\nSACRED HEART CHURCH\nWinter Regulation\n7:00 a. m. Mass and holy com\nmunion.\n9:15 a. m. Sunday school and Bi\nble class.\n10:00 a. m. High mass and ser\nmon.\n7:30 Vespers. Sermon, benediction\nof the blessed Sacrament.\ntar Society at ?:30 p. m.\nFirst Friday: Devotions to the\nSacred Heart, 7:00 a. m. and 7:00\np. m.\nFirst Sunday: Meeting of the\nChildren of Marfr, 1:30 pi m.\nSecond Sunday: Meeting of the\nHoly name Society 7:30 p. m.\nWeek Days: Divkpe service evg|*\nmorning at seven onjplock.\nJean B. Prlgon, q>. M. I LL. D\nl Pastor.\nCHURCH OF THT ADVENT\nI Episcopal,1\nChurch school and iBlbla class,\nHoly communion. 7:30\\*. m.\n9:30 m. V\nMii-nu-'g prayer and seirmon. 11\na. m.\nEvening service. 7:30 p. nik\nR. O. MACKINTOSH.\nMEXICAN METHODIST\n(Taylor and 13th Sta.)\n9:45\u2014Graded and departmental-\nlzed Sunday school. J. de la Pas\nGarcia, superintendent.\n7:30 p. m Preaching Service. You\nare all welcome to the house of\nGod.\nTuesday, 7:30 p. m.\u2014Prayer meet\ning.\nD. J. de la Oarza. pastor\nMOTHER GAVE\nBUCK-DRAUGHT\n\u201cFine for Constipation and\nSick Headache,\" Writes\nAlabama Lady.\nHuntsville, Ala.\u2014\"My mother\ngave Black-Draught to all tho\nchildren in our home\u201d writes Mrs.\nW. T. Taylor, of Sixth Avenue,\nthis city. \u201cIt was the only medi\ncine I knew of when I grew ujx\nWe took it in tho winter (as a\nlaxative) for colds, and whenever\nwe ate anything that disagreed\nwith us she gave us a course of\nBlack-Draught.\n\u201cAlter I grew up. I took Black\nDraught for constipation and sick\nheadache. It surely Is fine for that.\n\u201cI make a tea out of Black\nDraught and take It at night, when\nneeded. It Is the beet laxative\nknow anything about, and tho\nonly one I ever use. After a life\ntime of experience I can heartily\nrecommend It.\"\nThe medicine which this Ala\nbama lady reoommenda Is the\n\u00abuTv> Thedford's Black-DnoJUL.\nwhich so many others have Aid\nof having used, all their lives, be\ncause of the good results obtained\nfrom taking It.\nGet the genuine\u20141\u201cIhedford\u2018a\"\nNo other so good\u2014and none so\neconomical.\nm W J M M m *j mi'll\nA. TAMM\nBlue Printing and\nSupplies\nHarlingen, Texas\n1911 1930\nSkelton Abstract Co.\nAbstracts of Title Title Insurance\nMerchants Bank Building Brownsville\nDependable Phone 353 Prompt\nBROWNSVILLE TITLE COMPANY\nBROWNSVILLE. TEXAS\nAbstracts of Title Title Insurance\nWe cover all lands In Camcr\u00abn County\nCARNEIRO, CHUMNEY COMPANY\nCertified Public Accountants\nIncome Tax Service\nBROWNSVILLE SAN ANTONIO CORPUS CHRIST1\nState National Bank Smith-Young Tower Nixon Building\nPROSPERITY\nProsperity for Brownsville and\nthe Valley is a tangible, able-to\nbe-seen condition. Citrus groves\nare beginning to bloom vege\ntables are commanding good\nprices generally the interna\ntional airport and the bright\nprospects for a deep water port\u2014\nall are encouraging a splendid\nbusiness outlook for Brownsville\nand the Valley.\nLet us. as your bank, help\nyou with any problems you\nmay wish to discuss with us.\nFirst National Bank\nEst&blUhed in 1891\nBROWNSVILLE, TEXAS\nTITLE INSURANCE\nWhen you borrow money on real estate, many loan companies re\nquire the title to be insured. The best test of whether a title is\ninsurable, is to hare it insured. Require a title insurance policy\nwhen you bay.\nVALLEY ABSTRACT COMPANY\nPrompt Title Service\nBrownsville Edinburg\nOpposite Court House E. Harriman Blvd.\nPhefte 1181 Phone 93","height":"36368","width":"27328"}}
